{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875916963,"sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a73fe0e0017hKNX56DStPfJ5","messageID":"msg_d7a73ee05001UiSaLjvNXsGqfW","sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a7dbcc6f7a284b678d5dcab2c36f50ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n14: - **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n15: - **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### System Context\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         User CLI                                 │\n26: │  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent --provider k8s            │\n27: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n28:                               │\n29:                               ▼\n30: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n31: │                     CLI Layer (main.py)                          │\n32: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n33: │  │ Typer app.publish()                                       │   │\n34: │  │  - Parse CLI options                                      │   │\n35: │  │  - Create PublishRuntime                                  │   │\n36: │  │  - Handle errors (_handle_error)                          │   │\n37: │  │  - Display Rich Progress spinner                          │   │\n38: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                               │\n41:                               ▼\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                    Runtime Layer                                 │\n44: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n45: │  │ PublishRuntime.publish()                                  │   │\n46: │  │  1. Load metadata (MetadataService)                       │   │\n47: │  │  2. Apply option overrides                                │   │\n48: │  │  3. Prepare image (_prepare_image_for_publishing)         │   │\n49: │  │  4. Deploy via provider                                   │   │\n50: │  │  5. Update metadata                                       │   │\n51: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n52: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n53:                               │\n54:               ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n55:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n56: ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐\n57: │ AgentCube       │ │ Kubernetes      │ │ Docker          │\n58: │ Provider        │ │ Provider        │ │ Service         │\n59: │ (CR API)        │ │ (Deployment)    │ │ (Push)          │\n60: └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n61:               │               │               │\n62:               ▼               ▼               ▼\n63: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n64: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                            │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐     │\n66: │  │ AgentRuntime CR  │  │ Deployment + NodePort Service    │     │\n67: │  │ (agentcube)      │  │ (k8s)                            │     │\n68: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────┘     │\n69: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Component Diagram\n73: \n74: ```\n75: PublishRuntime\n76: ├── MetadataService (load/save metadata)\n77: ├── DockerService (push_image, login, tag)\n78: ├── Provider Selection\n79: │   ├── AgentCubeProvider (provider=\"agentcube\")\n80: │   │   ├── CustomObjectsApi (CR create/patch)\n81: │   │   ├── CoreV1Api (namespace)\n82: │   │   └── _sanitize_name()\n83: │   │   └── _ensure_namespace()\n84: │   └── KubernetesProvider (provider=\"k8s\")\n85: │       ├── AppsV1Api (Deployment)\n86: │       ├── CoreV1Api (Service, Namespace)\n87: │       ├── _create_deployment()\n88: │       ├── _create_service()\n89: │       ├── wait_for_deployment_ready()\n90: │       └── _sanitize_name()\n91: └── _update_publish_metadata()\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Data Structures\n97: \n98: ### AgentMetadata Extensions (Pydantic BaseModel)\n99: \n100: ```python\n101: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n102:     agent_name: str\n103:     description: Optional[str] = None\n104:     language: str = \"python\"\n105:     entrypoint: str\n106:     port: int = 8080\n107:     build_mode: str = \"local\"\n108:     region: Optional[str] = None\n109:     version: Optional[str] = None\n110:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n111:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n112:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n113:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n114:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n115:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n116:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n117:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n118:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n119:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n120:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n121:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None       # NEW: Assigned by AgentCube\n122:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n123:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # NEW: Deployment info\n124: \n125:     @validator(\"language\")\n126:     def validate_language(cls, v):\n127:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n128:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n129:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n130:         return v.lower()\n131: \n132:     @validator(\"build_mode\")\n133:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v):\n134:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n135:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n136:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n137:         return v.lower()\n138: \n139:     @validator(\"port\")\n140:     def validate_port(cls, v):\n141:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n142:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n143:         return v\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### k8s_deployment Field Structure\n147: \n148: ```python\n149: k8s_deployment: Dict[str, Any] = {\n150:     \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\" | \"Deployment\",\n151:     \"deployment_name\": str,\n152:     \"service_name\": str,           # k8s provider only\n153:     \"namespace\": str,\n154:     \"replicas\": int,\n155:     \"node_port\": int,              # k8s provider only\n156:     \"service_url\": str,            # k8s provider only: \"http://localhost:{node_port}\"\n157:     \"agent_id\": str,               # agentcube provider only\n158:     \"status\": \"created\" | \"ready\" | \"error\",\n159:     \"error\": Optional[str],        # Set on failure\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### PublishOptions (Internal)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: @dataclass\n167: class PublishOptions:\n168:     workspace: Path\n169:     version: Optional[str] = None\n170:     image_url: Optional[str] = None\n171:     image_username: Optional[str] = None\n172:     image_password: Optional[str] = None\n173:     description: Optional[str] = None\n174:     region: Optional[str] = None\n175:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n176:     provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n177:     node_port: Optional[int] = None\n178:     replicas: Optional[int] = None\n179:     namespace: Optional[str] = None\n180:     verbose: bool = False\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## API Contracts\n186: \n187: ### Typer Command Interface\n188: \n189: ```python\n190: @app.command()\n191: def publish(\n192:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", \n193:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n194:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\",\n195:         help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n196:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\",\n197:         help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n198:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\",\n199:         help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n200:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\",\n201:         help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n202:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\",\n203:         help=\"Agent description\"),\n204:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\",\n205:         help=\"Deployment region\"),\n206:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n207:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n208:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n209:         help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n210:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\",\n211:         help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n212:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\",\n213:         help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n214:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\",\n215:         help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n216:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\",\n217:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n218: ) -> None:\n219:     \"\"\"Deploy agent to Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n220:     try:\n221:         workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n222:         runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n223:         options = {\n224:             \"version\": version,\n225:             \"image_url\": image_url,\n226:             \"image_username\": image_username,\n227:             \"image_password\": image_password,\n228:             \"description\": description,\n229:             \"region\": region,\n230:             \"cloud_provider\": cloud_provider,\n231:             \"node_port\": node_port,\n232:             \"replicas\": replicas,\n233:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n234:         }\n235:         with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\")) as progress:\n236:             task = progress.add_task(\"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\", total=None)\n237:             result = runtime.publish(workspace_path, **options)\n238:             progress.remove_task(task)\n239:         \n240:         console.print(f\"[green]Successfully published agent![/green]\")\n241:         console.print(f\"  Agent Name: {result['agent_name']}\")\n242:         console.print(f\"  Agent ID: {result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}\")\n243:         console.print(f\"  Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n244:         console.print(f\"  Deployment Type: {result['deployment_type']}\")\n245:         console.print(f\"  Namespace: {result['namespace']}\")\n246:         \n247:     except Exception as e:\n248:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### PublishRuntime Contract\n252: \n253: ```python\n254: class PublishRuntime:\n255:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n256:         self.verbose = verbose\n257:         self.provider = provider\n258:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n259:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n260:         \n261:         if provider == \"k8s\":\n262:             self.k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n263:         elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n264:             self.agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n265:         else:\n266:             raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n267: \n268:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n269:         \"\"\"\n270:         Orchestrates the publish workflow.\n271:         \n272:         Returns:\n273:             Dict containing agent_name, agent_id, agent_endpoint, deployment_type, namespace, k8s_deployment\n274:         \"\"\"\n275:         ...\n276: \n277:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n278:         \"\"\"Deploy via AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n279:         ...\n280: \n281:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n282:         \"\"\"Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\"\"\"\n283:         ...\n284: \n285:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n286:         \"\"\"Return image URL ready for deployment.\"\"\"\n287:         ...\n288: \n289:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n290:         \"\"\"Push local Docker image to registry.\"\"\"\n291:         ...\n292: \n293:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n294:         \"\"\"Use cloud-built image URL.\"\"\"\n295:         ...\n296: \n297:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n298:         \"\"\"Persist deployment info to metadata YAML.\"\"\"\n299:         ...\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ### AgentCubeProvider Contract\n303: \n304: ```python\n305: class AgentCubeProvider:\n306:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n307:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n308:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n309:     \n310:     def __init__(\n311:         self,\n312:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n313:         verbose: bool = False,\n314:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n315:     ) -> None:\n316:         self.namespace = namespace\n317:         self.verbose = verbose\n318:         \n319:         if kubeconfig:\n320:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n321:         else:\n322:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n323:         \n324:         self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()\n325:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n326: \n327:     def deploy_agent_runtime(\n328:         self,\n329:         agent_name: str,\n330:         image_url: str,\n331:         port: int,\n332:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n333:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n334:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n335:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n336:         readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n337:         readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n338:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n339:         \"\"\"Create or patch AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n340:         ...\n341: \n342:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n343:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n344:         ...\n345: \n346:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n347:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n348:         ...\n349: \n350:     def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n351:         \"\"\"Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n352:         ...\n353: ```\n354: \n355: ### KubernetesProvider Contract\n356: \n357: ```python\n358: class KubernetesProvider:\n359:     NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000\n360:     NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767\n361:     DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120\n362:     POLL_INTERVAL = 2\n363:     \n364:     def __init__(\n365:         self,\n366:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n367:         verbose: bool = False,\n368:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n369:     ) -> None:\n370:         self.namespace = namespace\n371:         self.verbose = verbose\n372:         \n373:         if kubeconfig:\n374:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)\n375:         else:\n376:             kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()\n377:         \n378:         self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()\n379:         self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()\n380: \n381:     def deploy_agent(\n382:         self,\n383:         agent_name: str,\n384:         image_url: str,\n385:         port: int,\n386:         entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n387:         replicas: int = 1,\n388:         node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n389:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n390:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n391:         \"\"\"Create Deployment + NodePort Service and wait for ready.\"\"\"\n392:         ...\n393: \n394:     def _create_deployment(\n395:         self,\n396:         name: str,\n397:         image_url: str,\n398:         port: int,\n399:         entrypoint: Optional[str],\n400:         replicas: int,\n401:         env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n402:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n403:         \"\"\"Create Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n404:         ...\n405: \n406:     def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n407:         \"\"\"Create NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n408:         ...\n409: \n410:     def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n411:         \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n412:         ...\n413: \n414:     def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n415:         \"\"\"Get Deployment and Service status.\"\"\"\n416:         ...\n417: \n418:     def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n419:         \"\"\"Delete Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n420:         ...\n421: \n422:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None:\n423:         \"\"\"Create namespace if not exists.\"\"\"\n424:         ...\n425: \n426:     def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n427:         \"\"\"Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\"\"\"\n428:         ...\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ---\n432: \n433: ## Error Handling\n434: \n435: ### Error Categories\n436: \n437: | Category | Exception Type | Message Pattern | Recovery |\n438: |----------|----------------|-----------------|----------|\n439: | Metadata Missing | `ValueError` | `Missing required field: {field} in agent_metadata.yaml` | User must add field |\n440: | Provider Invalid | `ValueError` | `Invalid provider: {value}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'` | Use valid provider |\n441: | Image URL Missing | `ValueError` | `--image-url is required for local build mode` | Provide image URL |\n442: | Router URL Missing | `ValueError` | `router_url is required for agentcube provider in agent_metadata.yaml` | Add router_url |\n443: | Workload Manager Missing | `ValueError` | `workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider` | Add workload_manager_url |\n444: | NodePort Invalid | `ValueError` | `NodePort must be in range 30000-32767` | Use valid NodePort |\n445: | Docker Unavailable | `RuntimeError` | `Docker is not available or not running` | Start Docker |\n446: | Docker Push Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Failed to push image: {details}` | Check credentials |\n447: | K8s Unreachable | `RuntimeError` | `Kubernetes cluster is unreachable` | Check kubeconfig |\n448: | CRD Not Found | `ValueError` | `AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs` | Install CRDs |\n449: | Deployment Timeout | `TimeoutError` | `Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s` | Check pod logs |\n450: | Registry Auth Failed | `RuntimeError` | `Registry authentication failed: {details}` | Check credentials |\n451: \n452: ### Error Handling Pattern\n453: \n454: ```python\n455: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n456:     \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n457:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n458:     if verbose:\n459:         console.print_exception()\n460:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n461: ```\n462: \n463: ### Metadata Error Recording\n464: \n465: ```python\n466: def _record_error_in_metadata(workspace_path: Path, error_msg: str) -> None:\n467:     \"\"\"Record error in metadata before raising exception.\"\"\"\n468:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n469:     metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n470:         \"status\": \"error\",\n471:         \"error\": error_msg,\n472:     }\n473:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n474: ```\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## Testing Strategy\n479: \n480: ### Unit Tests\n481: \n482: | Test File | Coverage |\n483: |-----------|----------|\n484: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime orchestration, option overrides, provider selection |\n485: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | KubernetesProvider methods with mocked K8s API |\n486: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCubeProvider CR creation/patch with mocked API |\n487: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | push_image, login, tag methods |\n488: \n489: ### Mock Strategy\n490: \n491: ```python\n492: # Kubernetes API Mock\n493: @pytest.fixture\n494: def mock_k8s_api():\n495:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api\") as mock_apps:\n496:         with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\") as mock_core:\n497:             mock_apps.return_value.create_deployment.return_value = ...\n498:             mock_core.return_value.create_namespaced_service.return_value = ...\n499:             yield mock_apps, mock_core\n500: \n501: # AgentRuntime CR Mock\n502: @pytest.fixture\n503: def mock_custom_api():\n504:     with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\") as mock_custom:\n505:         mock_custom.return_value.create_custom_object.return_value = {\n506:             \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n507:             \"status\": {\"agentEndpoint\": \"http://test\"},\n508:         }\n509:         yield mock_custom\n510: \n511: # Docker Mock\n512: @pytest.fixture\n513: def mock_docker():\n514:     with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_client:\n515:         mock_client.return_value.images.push.return_value = [...]\n516:         yield mock_client\n517: ```\n518: \n519: ### Test Cases\n520: \n521: | Test Case | Scenario |\n522: |-----------|----------|\n523: | `test_publish_agentcube_success` | Valid metadata, agentcube provider, CR created |\n524: | `test_publish_k8s_success` | Valid metadata, k8s provider, Deployment + Service created |\n525: | `test_publish_missing_router_url` | agentcube provider without router_url raises ValueError |\n526: | `test_publish_missing_workload_manager` | agentcube provider without workload_manager_url raises ValueError |\n527: | `test_publish_invalid_provider` | Invalid provider raises ValueError |\n528: | `test_publish_image_url_required_local` | Local build mode without image_url raises ValueError |\n529: | `test_publish_node_port_out_of_range` | NodePort outside 30000-32767 raises ValueError |\n530: | `test_publish_deployment_timeout` | Deployment not ready after 120s raises TimeoutError |\n531: | `test_publish_metadata_update` | Metadata saved with agent_id and k8s_deployment |\n532: | `test_publish_error_metadata_update` | Error recorded in metadata before exception |\n533: | `test_k8s_provider_sanitize_name` | Name sanitized to DNS-compliant format |\n534: | `test_agentcube_provider_sanitize_name` | CR name sanitized |\n535: | `test_agentcube_provider_patch_existing_cr` | Patch instead of create for existing CR |\n536: | `test_docker_push_with_credentials` | Login + push with username/password |\n537: | `test_docker_push_without_credentials` | Push without login (pre-authenticated) |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## File Structure\n542: \n543: ```\n544: cmd/cli/\n545: ├── agentcube/\n546: │   ├── __init__.py                    # Package exports\n547: │   ├── cli/\n548: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n549: │   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app + publish command\n550: │   ├── runtime/\n551: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n552: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # (AR-020)\n553: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # (AR-021)\n554: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # NEW: PublishRuntime\n555: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # (AR-023)\n556: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          # (AR-024)\n557: │   ├── services/\n558: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n559: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # Load/save metadata\n560: │   │   ├── docker_service.py          # EXTEND: push_image, login, tag\n561: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # NEW: KubernetesProvider\n562: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # NEW: AgentCubeProvider\n563: │   └── models/\n564: │       ├── __init__.py\n565: │       └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions\n566: ├── tests/\n567: │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py        # NEW\n568: │   ├── test_k8s_provider.py           # NEW\n569: │   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py     # NEW\n570: │   └── test_docker_service.py         # EXTEND\n571: ├── pyproject.toml                     # Dependencies\n572: └── examples/\n573:     └── hello-agent/\n574:         ├── main.py\n575:         └── agent_metadata.yaml        # Example metadata\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ---\n579: \n580: ## Dependencies\n581: \n582: ### Runtime Dependencies\n583: \n584: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n585: |---------|---------|---------|\n586: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n587: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n588: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n589: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n590: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client (optional `[k8s]` extras) |\n591: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n592: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n593: | `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n594: \n595: ### pyproject.toml Optional Dependencies\n596: \n597: ```toml\n598: [project.optional-dependencies]\n599: k8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n600: dev = [\n601:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n602:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n603:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n604:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n605:     \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n606:     \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n607:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n608: ]\n609: test = [\n610:     \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n611:     \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n612:     \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n613:     \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n614:     \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n615: ]\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ---\n619: \n620: ## Implementation Notes\n621: \n622: ### Constants\n623: \n624: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n625: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n626: | `CR_GROUP` | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n627: | `CR_VERSION` | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n628: | `CR_PLURAL` | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n629: | `SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default session timeout |\n630: | `MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default max session duration |\n631: | `DEFAULT_SECRET` | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default imagePullSecret |\n632: | `NODE_PORT_MIN` | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n633: | `NODE_PORT_MAX` | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n634: | `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Deployment readiness timeout |\n635: | `POLL_INTERVAL` | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Status poll interval (seconds) |\n636: \n637: ### AgentRuntime CR Template\n638: \n639: ```python\n640: cr_body = {\n641:     \"apiVersion\": f\"{self.CR_GROUP}/{self.CR_VERSION}\",\n642:     \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n643:     \"metadata\": {\n644:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n645:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n646:     },\n647:     \"spec\": {\n648:         \"image\": image_url,\n649:         \"port\": port,\n650:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n651:         \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n652:         \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n653:         \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n654:         \"env\": [\n655:             {\"name\": \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\", \"value\": workload_manager_url},\n656:             {\"name\": \"ROUTER_URL\", \"value\": router_url},\n657:         ],\n658:         \"readinessProbe\": {\n659:             \"httpGet\": {\n660:                 \"path\": readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n661:                 \"port\": readiness_probe_port or port,\n662:             },\n663:         },\n664:     },\n665: }\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ### Kubernetes Deployment Template\n669: \n670: ```python\n671: deployment_body = {\n672:     \"apiVersion\": \"apps/v1\",\n673:     \"kind\": \"Deployment\",\n674:     \"metadata\": {\n675:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n676:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n677:         \"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n678:     },\n679:     \"spec\": {\n680:         \"replicas\": replicas,\n681:         \"selector\": {\"matchLabels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n682:         \"template\": {\n683:             \"metadata\": {\"labels\": {\"app\": sanitized_name}},\n684:             \"spec\": {\n685:                 \"containers\": [{\n686:                     \"name\": sanitized_name,\n687:                     \"image\": image_url,\n688:                     \"ports\": [{\"containerPort\": port}],\n689:                     \"env\": [{\"name\": k, \"value\": v} for k, v in (env_vars or {}).items()],\n690:                 }],\n691:             },\n692:         },\n693:     },\n694: }\n695: ```\n696: \n697: ### NodePort Service Template\n698: \n699: ```python\n700: service_body = {\n701:     \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n702:     \"kind\": \"Service\",\n703:     \"metadata\": {\n704:         \"name\": sanitized_name,\n705:         \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n706:     },\n707:     \"spec\": {\n708:         \"type\": \"NodePort\",\n709:         \"selector\": {\"app\": sanitized_name},\n710:         \"ports\": [{\n711:             \"port\": port,\n712:             \"targetPort\": port,\n713:             \"nodePort\": node_port,  # Optional, K8s auto-assigns if None\n714:         }],\n715:     },\n716: }\n717: ```\n718: \n719: ### Name Sanitization Algorithm\n720: \n721: ```python\n722: def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str:\n723:     \"\"\"\n724:     Convert to lowercase DNS-compliant name (max 63 chars).\n725:     Rules:\n726:     - Lowercase only\n727:     - Replace non-alphanumeric with '-'\n728:     - Truncate to 63 characters\n729:     - Remove leading/trailing '-'\n730:     \"\"\"\n731:     sanitized = name.lower()\n732:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", sanitized)\n733:     sanitized = re.sub(r\"-+\", \"-\", sanitized)\n734:     sanitized = sanitized.strip(\"-\")\n735:     return sanitized[:63]\n736: ```\n737: \n738: ### Wait for Deployment Ready Algorithm\n739: \n740: ```python\n741: def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n742:     start = time.time()\n743:     while time.time() - start < timeout:\n744:         deployment = self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment(name, self.namespace)\n745:         if deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas:\n746:             return\n747:         time.sleep(self.POLL_INTERVAL)\n748:     raise TimeoutError(f\"Deployment {name} not ready after {timeout}s\")\n749: ```\n750: \n751: ---\n752: \n753: ## References\n754: \n755: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n756: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (publish command requirements)\n757: - deployment/spec.md — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n758: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n759: - AR-021 — CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n760: - AR-023 — CLI invoke command\n761: - AR-024 — CLI status command\n762: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n763: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n764: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n765: - Volcano AgentCube CRD: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n\n(End of file - total 765 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `publish` command orchestrates agent deployment to Kubernetes via two providers:\n- **agentcube**: Creates `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) for Volcano AgentCube integration\n- **k8s**: Creates standard Kubernetes `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775875916940,"end":1775875916960}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875916966,"sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a740486001AcFWNWZvn15C6Q","messageID":"msg_d7a73ee05001UiSaLjvNXsGqfW","sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3f2e4cc058b045baaf805c61324cd51d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                           Developer Environment                          │\n24: │  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐               │\n25: │  │   Terminal   │───▶│  kubectl-    │───▶│  Workspace   │               │\n26: │  │   (CLI)      │    │  agentcube   │    │  Directory   │               │\n27: │  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘               │\n28: │                              │                                           │\n29: │                              ▼                                           │\n30: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n31: │                    │ agent_metadata.  │                                  │\n32: │                    │ yaml             │                                  │\n33: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n34: │                              │                                           │\n35: │                              ▼                                           │\n36: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                                  │\n37: │                    │ Dockerfile       │ (generated if missing)           │\n38: │                    └──────────────────┐                                  │\n39: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Component Diagram\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                         agentcube/cli/main.py                            │\n47: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n48: │  │                        Typer App                                  │   │\n49: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  │   │\n50: │  │  │   pack()   │  │   build()  │  │  publish() │  │  invoke()  │  │   │\n51: │  │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │  command   │  │   │\n52: │  │  └─────┬──────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  │   │\n53: │  └───────│──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n54: │          │                                                               │\n55: └──────────│───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n56:            ▼\n57: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n58: │                      agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py                   │\n59: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n60: │  │                      PackRuntime                                  │   │\n61: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n62: │  │  │   pack()        │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_load_or_create_ │   │   │\n63: │  │  │   (main entry)  │  │workspace_        │  │metadata()       │   │   │\n64: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │structure()       │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n65: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n66: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n67: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n68: │  │  │_apply_option_   │──▶│_validate_       │──▶│_process_       │   │   │\n69: │  │  │overrides()      │  │language_         │  │dependencies()   │   │   │\n70: │  │  └─────────────────┘  │compatibility()   │  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n71: │  │                       └─────────────────┘           │             │   │\n72: │  │                                                       ▼             │   │\n73: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │   │\n74: │  │  │_generate_       │──▶│_update_pack_    │──▶│_prepare_output_ │   │   │\n75: │  │  │dockerfile()     │  │metadata()       │  │path()           │   │   │\n76: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │   │\n77: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n78: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n79:            │\n80:            ▼\n81: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │                      agentcube/services/                                 │\n83: │  ┌───────────────────────┐        ┌───────────────────────┐            │\n84: │  │   MetadataService     │        │     DockerService     │            │\n85: │  │  (metadata_service.py)│        │  (docker_service.py)  │            │\n86: │  │  - load_metadata()    │        │  - check_docker_      │            │\n87: │  │  - save_metadata()    │        │    available()        │            │\n88: │  │  - validate_workspace │        │  - build_image()      │            │\n89: │  └───────────────────────┘        └───────────────────────┘            │\n90: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n91:            │\n92:            ▼\n93: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n94: │                      agentcube/models/pack_models.py                     │\n95: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n96: │  │                    MetadataOptions                                │   │\n97: │  │  - agent_name: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n98: │  │  - language: Optional[str] = 'python'                             │   │\n99: │  │  - entrypoint: Optional[str]                                      │   │\n100: │  │  - port: Optional[int] = 8080                                     │   │\n101: │  │  - build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'                            │   │\n102: │  │  - description: Optional[str]                                     │   │\n103: │  │  - from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])                     │   │\n104: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n105: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### Request Flow\n109: \n110: ```\n111: User                    CLI (main.py)              PackRuntime           Services\n112:  │                          │                          │                    │\n113:  │ kubectl-agentcube pack   │                          │                    │\n114:  │─────────────────────────▶│                          │                    │\n115:  │                          │ PackRuntime(verbose)     │                    │\n116:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n117:  │                          │                          │                    │\n118:  │                          │ pack(workspace, options) │                    │\n119:  │                          │─────────────────────────▶│                    │\n120:  │                          │                          │                    │\n121:  │                          │                          │ _validate_workspace│\n122:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n123:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n124:  │                          │                          │                    │\n125:  │                          │                          │ _load_or_create    │\n126:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n127:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n128:  │                          │                          │  AgentMetadata     │\n129:  │                          │                          │                    │\n130:  │                          │                          │ _apply_overrides   │\n131:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n132:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n133:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n134:  │                          │                          │  merged metadata   │\n135:  │                          │                          │                    │\n136:  │                          │                          │ _validate_language │\n137:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n138:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n139:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n140:  │                          │                          │                    │\n141:  │                          │                          │ _process_deps      │\n142:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n143:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n144:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n145:  │                          │                          │                    │\n146:  │                          │                          │ _generate_dockerfile\n147:  │                          │                          │─────────┐          │\n148:  │                          │                          │         │          │\n149:  │                          │                          │◀────────┘          │\n150:  │                          │                          │  Dockerfile path   │\n151:  │                          │                          │                    │\n152:  │                          │                          │ _update_pack_metadata\n153:  │                          │                          │───────────────────▶│\n154:  │                          │                          │◀───────────────────│\n155:  │                          │                          │                    │\n156:  │                          │◀─────────────────────────│                    │\n157:  │                          │  result dict             │                    │\n158:  │                          │                          │                    │\n159:  │◀─────────────────────────│                          │                    │\n160:  │  Success message with    │                          │                    │\n161:  │  agent_name, paths       │                          │                    │\n162:  │                          │                          │                    │\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Data Structures\n168: \n169: ### `MetadataOptions` (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n173: from typing import Optional, Any, Dict\n174: \n175: @dataclass\n176: class MetadataOptions:\n177:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n178:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n179:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n180:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n181:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n182:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n183:     description: Optional[str] = None\n184:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n185:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n186:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n187:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n188:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n189:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n190:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n191:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n192: \n193:     @classmethod\n194:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n195:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### `AgentMetadata` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n199: \n200: ```python\n201: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n202: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n203: \n204: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n205:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n206:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n207:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n208:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n209:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n210:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n211:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n212:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n213:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n214:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n215:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n216:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n217:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n218:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n219:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n220:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n221:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n222:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n223:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n224:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n225:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n226:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n227: \n228:     @field_validator('language')\n229:     @classmethod\n230:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n231:         allowed = ['python', 'java']\n232:         v_lower = v.lower()\n233:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n234:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n235:         return v_lower\n236: \n237:     @field_validator('build_mode')\n238:     @classmethod\n239:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n240:         allowed = ['local', 'cloud']\n241:         v_lower = v.lower()\n242:         if v_lower not in allowed:\n243:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n244:         return v_lower\n245: \n246:     @field_validator('port')\n247:     @classmethod\n248:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n249:         if not 1 <= v <= 65535:\n250:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n251:         return v\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: from pathlib import Path\n258: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n259: \n260: class PackRuntime:\n261:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n262:         self.verbose = verbose\n263:         self._metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose)\n264:         self._docker_service = DockerService(verbose)\n265: \n266:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n267:         result = {\n268:             \"agent_name\": None,\n269:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n270:             \"metadata_path\": None,\n271:             \"dockerfile_path\": None,\n272:             \"status\": \"pending\"\n273:         }\n274:         try:\n275:             self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n276:             metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n277:             metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n278:             self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n279:             self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n280:             dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n281:             self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n282:             output_path = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n283:             \n284:             result[\"agent_name\"] = metadata.agent_name\n285:             result[\"metadata_path\"] = str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\")\n286:             result[\"dockerfile_path\"] = str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None\n287:             result[\"status\"] = \"success\"\n288:         except Exception as e:\n289:             result[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n290:             result[\"error\"] = str(e)\n291:             raise\n292:         return result\n293: \n294:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n295:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n296:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n297:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n298:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n299: \n300:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n301:         metadata_files = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n302:         for filename in metadata_files:\n303:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n304:             if filepath.exists():\n305:                 return self._metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n306:         \n307:         agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n308:         return AgentMetadata(\n309:             agent_name=agent_name,\n310:             language=options.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n311:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\") or self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, \"python\"),\n312:             port=options.get(\"port\", 8080),\n313:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n314:             description=options.get(\"description\", \"\")\n315:         )\n316: \n317:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n318:         updates = {}\n319:         if options.get(\"agent_name\"):\n320:             updates[\"agent_name\"] = options[\"agent_name\"]\n321:         if options.get(\"language\"):\n322:             updates[\"language\"] = options[\"language\"]\n323:         if options.get(\"entrypoint\"):\n324:             updates[\"entrypoint\"] = options[\"entrypoint\"]\n325:         if options.get(\"port\"):\n326:             updates[\"port\"] = options[\"port\"]\n327:         if options.get(\"build_mode\"):\n328:             updates[\"build_mode\"] = options[\"build_mode\"]\n329:         if options.get(\"description\"):\n330:             updates[\"description\"] = options[\"description\"]\n331:         \n332:         for key, value in updates.items():\n333:             setattr(metadata, key, value)\n334:         return metadata\n335: \n336:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n337:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n338:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n339:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n340:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n341: \n342:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n343:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n344:         if not py_files:\n345:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n346: \n347:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n348:         pom_file = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n349:         if not pom_file.exists():\n350:             raise ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in Java workspace\")\n351: \n352:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n353:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n354:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path)\n355:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n356:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n357: \n358:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n359:         requirements_file = workspace_path / \"requirements.txt\"\n360:         if requirements_file.exists():\n361:             pass\n362: \n363:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n364:         pass\n365: \n366:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n367:         dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n368:         if dockerfile_path.exists():\n369:             return dockerfile_path\n370:         \n371:         content = \"\"\n372:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n373:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n374:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n375:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n376:         \n377:         dockerfile_path.write_text(content)\n378:         return dockerfile_path\n379: \n380:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n381:         return f'''FROM python:3.10-slim\n382: WORKDIR /app\n383: COPY requirements.txt .\n384: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n385: COPY . .\n386: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n387: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n388: '''\n389: \n390:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n391:         return f'''FROM maven:3.8-openjdk-17 as build\n392: WORKDIR /app\n393: COPY pom.xml .\n394: RUN mvn dependency:go-offline\n395: COPY . .\n396: RUN mvn package -DskipTests\n397: FROM openjdk:17-slim\n398: WORKDIR /app\n399: COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\n400: EXPOSE {metadata.port}\n401: CMD [{metadata.entrypoint}]\n402: '''\n403: \n404:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n405:         if dockerfile_path:\n406:             metadata.image = {\"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path)}\n407:         self._metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n408: \n409:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n410:         if output_path:\n411:             return Path(output_path)\n412:         return workspace_path / \"packaged\"\n413: \n414:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n415:         if language == \"python\":\n416:             main_py = workspace_path / \"main.py\"\n417:             if main_py.exists():\n418:                 return \"python, main.py\"\n419:             py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n420:             if py_files:\n421:                 return f\"python, {py_files[0].name}\"\n422:         elif language == \"java\":\n423:             return \"java, -jar, app.jar\"\n424:         return \"\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: ---\n428: \n429: ## API Contracts\n430: \n431: ### Command Interface\n432: \n433: | Command | Arguments | Description |\n434: |---------|-----------|-------------|\n435: | `pack` | `-f/--workspace` (default: `.`) | Path to agent workspace directory |\n436: | | `--agent-name` | Override agent name (Optional) |\n437: | | `--language` | Programming language: python, java (Optional) |\n438: | | `--entrypoint` | Override entrypoint command (Optional) |\n439: | | `--port` | Port to expose in Dockerfile (Optional, int) |\n440: | | `--build-mode` | Build strategy: local or cloud (Optional) |\n441: | | `--description` | Agent description (Optional) |\n442: | | `--output` | Output path for packaged workspace (Optional) |\n443: | | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging (bool, default: False) |\n444: \n445: ### Typer Command Signature\n446: \n447: ```python\n448: @app.command()\n449: def pack(\n450:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n451:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n452:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n453:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n454:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n455:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n456:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n457:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n458:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n459: ) -> None:\n460:     \"\"\"Validate and prepare agent workspace for building.\"\"\"\n461:     from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n462:     \n463:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n464:     options = {\n465:         \"agent_name\": agent_name,\n466:         \"language\": language,\n467:         \"entrypoint\": entrypoint,\n468:         \"port\": port,\n469:         \"build_mode\": build_mode,\n470:         \"description\": description,\n471:         \"output\": output,\n472:     }\n473:     \n474:     try:\n475:         with Progress(\n476:             SpinnerColumn(),\n477:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n478:         ) as progress:\n479:             task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n480:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose)\n481:             result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n482:         \n483:         console.print(f\"[green]Success![/green] Agent [bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold] packed.\")\n484:         console.print(f\"  Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n485:         console.print(f\"  Metadata:  {result['metadata_path']}\")\n486:         if result['dockerfile_path']:\n487:             console.print(f\"  Dockerfile: {result['dockerfile_path']}\")\n488:     except Exception as e:\n489:         _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n490: ```\n491: \n492: ### Metadata File Format\n493: \n494: ```yaml\n495: agent_name: my-agent\n496: description: Example agent\n497: language: python\n498: entrypoint: python, main.py\n499: port: 8080\n500: build_mode: local\n501: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n502: version: null\n503: image:\n504:   dockerfile_path: /path/to/workspace/Dockerfile\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ## Error Handling\n510: \n511: ### Exit Codes\n512: \n513: | Code | Condition | Error Message |\n514: |------|-----------|---------------|\n515: | `1` | Workspace does not exist | `Workspace directory does not exist: {path}` |\n516: | `1` | Workspace is not a directory | `Workspace path is not a directory: {path}` |\n517: | `1` | No Python files in workspace | `No Python files found in workspace` |\n518: | `1` | No pom.xml in Java workspace | `No pom.xml found in Java workspace` |\n519: | `1` | Invalid language | Pydantic validation error |\n520: | `1` | Invalid build_mode | Pydantic validation error |\n521: | `1` | Invalid port range | Pydantic validation error |\n522: | `1` | PackRuntime.pack raises | `Error packaging agent: {e}` (with traceback if verbose) |\n523: \n524: ### Error Handler Implementation\n525: \n526: ```python\n527: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n528:     from rich.console import Console\n529:     console = Console()\n530:     \n531:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n532:     if verbose:\n533:         import traceback\n534:         console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n535:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## Testing Strategy\n541: \n542: ### Unit Tests\n543: \n544: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n545: |-----------|-------|----------|\n546: | `test_pack_valid_python_workspace` | Valid Python workspace with main.py | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n547: | `test_pack_valid_java_workspace` | Valid Java workspace with pom.xml | Success with metadata_path, dockerfile_path |\n548: | `test_pack_missing_workspace` | Non-existent path | ValueError \"Workspace directory does not exist\" |\n549: | `test_pack_not_directory` | File path instead of directory | ValueError \"Workspace path is not a directory\" |\n550: | `test_pack_python_no_py_files` | Directory with no .py files | ValueError \"No Python files found\" |\n551: | `test_pack_java_no_pom` | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError \"No pom.xml found\" |\n552: | `test_pack_override_agent_name` | `--agent-name custom-name` | metadata.agent_name == \"custom-name\" |\n553: | `test_pack_override_language` | `--language java` | metadata.language == \"java\" |\n554: | `test_pack_override_port` | `--port 9000` | metadata.port == 9000 |\n555: | `test_pack_invalid_language` | `--language ruby` | Pydantic validation error |\n556: | `test_pack_invalid_port` | `--port 70000` | Pydantic validation error \"port must be 1-65535\" |\n557: | `test_pack_existing_dockerfile` | Workspace with pre-existing Dockerfile | Dockerfile not regenerated, path returned |\n558: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_python` | Python workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Python template |\n559: | `test_pack_generate_dockerfile_java` | Java workspace, no Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated with Java template |\n560: | `test_pack_metadata_fallback` | Workspace with agent.yaml (no agent_metadata.yaml) | Loads from agent.yaml |\n561: \n562: ### Integration Tests\n563: \n564: | Scenario | Description |\n565: |----------|-------------|\n566: | `test_pack_full_flow_python` | End-to-end: create temp Python workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n567: | `test_pack_full_flow_java` | End-to-end: create temp Java workspace → pack → verify metadata + Dockerfile |\n568: | `test_pack_with_existing_metadata` | Workspace with agent_metadata.yaml → pack preserves and updates metadata |\n569: | `test_pack_cli_integration` | Run `kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path` via subprocess, verify exit code and output |\n570: | `test_pack_verbose_output` | Pack with --verbose, verify detailed logs printed |\n571: | `test_pack_output_path` | Pack with --output /custom/path, verify packaged artifacts location |\n572: \n573: ---\n574: \n575: ## File Structure\n576: \n577: ```\n578: cmd/cli/\n579: ├── pyproject.toml                  # Project metadata, dependencies, console scripts\n580: ├── agentcube/\n581: │   ├── __init__.py                 # Package version, exports app + runtimes\n582: │   ├── cli/\n583: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # CLI subpackage marker\n584: │   │   └ main.py                   # Typer app, pack command, _handle_error\n585: │   ├── models/\n586: │   │   └ pack_models.py            # MetadataOptions dataclass\n587: │   ├── runtime/\n588: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Re-exports PackRuntime + MetadataOptions\n589: │   │   └ pack_runtime.py           # PackRuntime class\n590: │   ├── services/\n591: │   │   ├── __init__.py             # Services package docstring\n592: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py     # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n593: │   │   ├── docker_service.py       # DockerService (for build validation)\n594: │   ├── operations/\n595: │   │   └ __init__.py               # Placeholder (no symbols)\n596: ├── examples/\n597: │   ├── hello-agent/\n598: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n599: │   ├── math-agent/\n600: │   │   └ main.py                   # Example Python agent\n601: └── tests/\n602:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py        # PackRuntime unit tests\n603:     ├── test_pack_cli.py            # CLI pack command tests\n604:     └ test_metadata_service.py      # MetadataService tests\n605: ```\n606: \n607: ---\n608: \n609: ## Dependencies\n610: \n611: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n612: |---------|---------|---------|\n613: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework with Rich support |\n614: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation and serialization |\n615: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML metadata file parsing |\n616: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Progress spinner, colored output |\n617: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK (optional, for validation) |\n618: | `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n619: | `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mocking for unit tests |\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## Implementation Notes\n624: \n625: ### Metadata File Resolution Order\n626: \n627: The `pack` command loads metadata from files in this order (first match wins):\n628: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (primary)\n629: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n630: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n631: \n632: If none exist, new metadata is created based on CLI options and workspace defaults.\n633: \n634: ### Entrypoint Inference\n635: \n636: When `--entrypoint` is not provided:\n637: - Python: Look for `main.py` → `\"python, main.py\"`; else first `.py` file → `\"python, {filename}\"`\n638: - Java: Default → `\"java, -jar, app.jar\"`\n639: \n640: ### Dockerfile Generation Logic\n641: \n642: 1. If `Dockerfile` exists in workspace → return existing path (no regeneration)\n643: 2. If missing → generate based on `metadata.language`:\n644:    - Python: Multi-stage with `pip install` from requirements.txt\n645:    - Java: Multi-stage Maven build → slim JRE runtime\n646: \n647: ### Metadata Save Format\n648: \n649: ```yaml\n650: # agent_metadata.yaml\n651: agent_name: my-agent\n652: description: \"Example agent\"\n653: language: python\n654: entrypoint: \"python, main.py\"\n655: port: 8080\n656: build_mode: local\n657: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n658: image:\n659:   dockerfile_path: ./Dockerfile\n660: ```\n661: \n662: YAML dump settings:\n663: - `default_flow_style=False`\n664: - `indent=2`\n665: - `sort_keys=False`\n666: - Exclude `None` fields: `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n667: \n668: ---\n669: \n670: ## References\n671: \n672: - cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n673: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (pack, build, publish, invoke, status)\n674: - AR-021 — CLI build command (follows pack)\n675: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build)\n\n(End of file - total 675 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe `pack` command validates and prepares an agent workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and reports paths. It is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status).\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-020/design.md","time":{"start":1775875916946,"end":1775875916964}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875916971,"sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a740086001tLGE630nX2yPdy","messageID":"msg_d7a73ee05001UiSaLjvNXsGqfW","sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-08fd3ac15abf4e7397247ecf20373379","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Build command for AgentCube CLI that constructs container images from packaged agent workspaces. Orchestrates the full build lifecycle: prerequisite validation, version increment, Docker SDK build execution, and metadata persistence.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                        User Environment                          │\n24: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n25: │                                                                  │\n26: │   ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐    │\n27: │   │ Agent        │     │ agent_       │     │ Dockerfile   │    │\n28: │   │ Workspace    │────▶│ metadata.    │────▶│ (generated   │    │\n29: │   │ (./my-agent) │     │ yaml         │     │ by pack)     │    │\n30: │   └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘    │\n31: │          │                   │                    │              │\n32: │          └───────────────────┴────────────────────┘              │\n33: │                              │                                   │\n34: │                              ▼                                   │\n35: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                          │\n36: │                    │ kubectl-agentcube│                          │\n37: │                    │     build -f .   │                          │\n38: │                    └──────────────────┘                          │\n39: │                              │                                   │\n40: └──────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────┘\n41:                                │\n42:                                ▼\n43: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                     AgentCube CLI                                │\n45: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n46: │                                                                  │\n47: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n48: │   │                  CLI Layer (main.py)                     │   │\n49: │   │  ┌─────────┐                                             │   │\n50: │   │  │ build() │  Typer command handler                      │   │\n51: │   │  │         │  - Parse options                            │   │\n52: │   │  │         │  - Rich Progress spinner                    │   │\n53: │   │  │         │  - Error handling via _handle_error         │   │\n54: │   │  └─────────┘                                             │   │\n55: │   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n56: │                           │                                      │\n57: │                           ▼                                      │\n58: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n59: │   │                Runtime Layer                             │   │\n60: │   │  ┌──────────────┐                                        │   │\n61: │   │  │ BuildRuntime │  Orchestration class                   │   │\n62: │   │  │              │  - build() main entry                  │   │\n63: │   │  │              │  - _increment_version()                │   │\n64: │   │  │              │  - _validate_build_prerequisites()    │   │\n65: │   │  │              │  - _build_local() / _build_cloud()    │   │\n66: │   │  │              │  - _update_build_metadata()           │   │\n67: │   │  └──────────────┘                                        │   │\n68: │   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n69: │                           │                                      │\n70: │                           ▼                                      │\n71: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n72: │   │                Service Layer                             │   │\n73: │   │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                     │   │\n74: │   │  │ DockerService│  │MetadataService│                    │   │\n75: │   │  │              │  │               │                     │   │\n76: │   │  │ - check_     │  │ - load_       │                     │   │\n77: │   │  │   docker_    │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n78: │   │  │   available()│  │ - save_       │                     │   │\n79: │   │  │ - build_     │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n80: │   │  │   image()    │  │               │                     │   │\n81: │   │  │ - get_       │  │               │                     │   │\n82: │   │  │   image_     │  │               │                     │   │\n83: │   │  │   info()     │  │               │                     │   │\n84: │   │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                     │   │\n85: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n86: │                                                                  │\n87: └───────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┘\n88:                                 │\n89:                                 ▼\n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                     External Systems                             │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │                                                                  │\n94: │   ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐                    │\n95: │   │ Docker       │          │ Metadata     │                    │\n96: │   │ Daemon       │◀────────▶│ YAML File    │                    │\n97: │   │ (dockerd)    │          │ (workspace)  │                    │\n98: │   └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘                    │\n99: │                                                                  │\n100: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Component Diagram\n104: \n105: ```\n106: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n107: │                         agentcube/runtime/                          │\n108: ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n109: │                                                                     │\n110: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n111: │  │                    BuildRuntime                               │  │\n112: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  │\n113: │  │ Fields:                                                       │  │\n114: │  │   - verbose: bool                                             │  │\n115: │  │   - docker_service: DockerService                             │  │\n116: │  │   - metadata_service: MetadataService                         │  │\n117: │  │                                                               │  │\n118: │  │ Methods:                                                      │  │\n119: │  │   + build(workspace_path: Path, **options) → Dict[str, Any]   │  │\n120: │  │   + _increment_version(workspace_path, metadata) → str       │  │\n121: │  │   + _validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path) → None     │  │\n122: │  │   + _build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n123: │  │   + _build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n124: │  │   + _update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata,         │  │\n125: │  │                           build_result, tag) → None           │  │\n126: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n127: │                                                                     │\n128: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n129: \n130: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n131: │                         agentcube/services/                        │\n132: ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n133: │                                                                     │\n134: │  ┌────────────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐    │\n135: │  │       DockerService        │  │      MetadataService       │    │\n136: │  ├────────────────────────────┤  ├────────────────────────────┤    │\n137: │  │ Fields:                    │  │ Fields:                    │    │\n138: │  │   - verbose: bool          │  │   - verbose: bool          │    │\n139: │  │   - client: DockerClient   │  │                            │    │\n140: │  │                            │  │ Methods:                   │    │\n141: │  │ Methods:                   │  │   + load_metadata()        │    │\n142: │  │   + check_docker_available│  │   + save_metadata()        │    │\n143: │  │   + build_image()          │  │   + update_metadata()      │    │\n144: │  │   + get_image_info()       │  │                            │    │\n145: │  │   + push_image()           │  │                            │    │\n146: │  │   + remove_image()         │  │                            │    │\n147: │  └────────────────────────────┘  └────────────────────────────┘    │\n148: │                                                                     │\n149: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ### Request Flow\n153: \n154: ```\n155: User Input: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --verbose\n156: \n157:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n158:                 │  CLI Entry (main.py)                    │\n159:                 │                                         │\n160:                 │  1. Parse Typer options                 │\n161:                 │     - workspace: str                    │\n162:                 │     - proxy: Optional[str]              │\n163:                 │     - cloud_provider: Optional[str]     │\n164:                 │     - output: Optional[str]             │\n165:                 │     - verbose: bool                     │\n166:                 │                                         │\n167:                 │  2. Initialize BuildRuntime(verbose)    │\n168:                 │                                         │\n169:                 │  3. Start Rich Progress spinner         │\n170:                 │                                         │\n171:                 │  4. Call runtime.build(workspace, ...)  │\n172:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n173:                                  │\n174:                                  ▼\n175:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n176:                 │  BuildRuntime.build()                   │\n177:                 │                                         │\n178:                 │  Step 1: Load metadata                  │\n179:                 │     metadata_service.load_metadata()    │\n180:                 │     → AgentMetadata                     │\n181:                 │                                         │\n182:                 │  Step 2: Validate prerequisites         │\n183:                 │     _validate_build_prerequisites()     │\n184:                 │     - Check Docker available            │\n185:                 │     - Check Dockerfile exists           │\n186:                 │                                         │\n187:                 │  Step 3: Increment version              │\n188:                 │     original_version = metadata.version │\n189:                 │     new_tag = _increment_version()      │\n190:                 │     - X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1)                 │\n191:                 │     - v1.0 → v1.0.1                     │\n192:                 │     - None → \"latest\"                   │\n193:                 │                                         │\n194:                 │  Step 4: Execute build                  │\n195:                 │     if build_mode == \"local\":           │\n196:                 │         result = _build_local()         │\n197:                 │     else:                               │\n198:                 │         result = _build_cloud()         │\n199:                 │                                         │\n200:                 │  Step 5: Handle result                  │\n201:                 │     if success:                         │\n202:                 │         _update_build_metadata()        │\n203:                 │         return result                   │\n204:                 │     if failure:                         │\n205:                 │         rollback version to original    │\n206:                 │         raise RuntimeError              │\n207:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n208:                                  │\n209:                                  ▼\n210:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n211:                 │  BuildRuntime._build_local()            │\n212:                 │                                         │\n213:                 │  1. Resolve image name                  │\n214:                 │     image_name = f\"{agent_name}:{tag}\"  │\n215:                 │                                         │\n216:                 │  2. Build with Docker SDK               │\n217:                 │     docker_service.build_image(         │\n218:                 │         dockerfile_path=workspace/      │\n219:                 │                       Dockerfile,       │\n220:                 │         context_path=workspace,         │\n221:                 │         image_name=image_name,          │\n222:                 │         tag=tag,                        │\n223:                 │         build_args={                    │\n224:                 │             \"PROXY\": proxy              │\n225:                 │         } if proxy else None            │\n226:                 │     )                                   │\n227:                 │                                         │\n228:                 │  3. Get image info                      │\n229:                 │     docker_service.get_image_info()     │\n230:                 │     → image_id, image_size              │\n231:                 │                                         │\n232:                 │  4. Return build result dict            │\n233:                 │     {                                   │\n234:                 │         \"image_name\": \"...\",            │\n235:                 │         \"image_id\": \"...\",              │\n236:                 │         \"image_size\": \"...\",            │\n237:                 │         \"build_time\": \"...\",            │\n238:                 │         \"tag\": tag                      │\n239:                 │     }                                   │\n240:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n241:                                  │\n242:                                  ▼\n243:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n244:                 │  DockerService.build_image()            │\n245:                 │                                         │\n246:                 │  1. Get Docker client                   │\n247:                 │     client = docker.from_env()          │\n248:                 │                                         │\n249:                 │  2. Build image with streaming          │\n250:                 │     for line in client.api.build(       │\n251:                 │         path=str(context_path),         │\n252:                 │         dockerfile=str(dockerfile),     │\n253:                 │         tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",      │\n254:                 │         buildargs=build_args,           │\n255:                 │         decode=True                     │\n256:                 │     ):                                  │\n257:                 │         if verbose: log each line      │\n258:                 │                                         │\n259:                 │  3. Measure build time                  │\n260:                 │     start_time → end_time               │\n261:                 │                                         │\n262:                 │  4. Return structured result            │\n263:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n264:                                  │\n265:                                  ▼\n266:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n267:                 │  CLI Output                             │\n268:                 │                                         │\n269:                 │  Success:                               │\n270:                 │    [green] Build completed successfully │\n271:                 │    Image: {image_name}:{tag}            │\n272:                 │    Image ID: {image_id}                 │\n273:                 │    Size: {image_size}                   │\n274:                 │    Build time: {build_time}s            │\n275:                 │                                         │\n276:                 │  Failure:                               │\n277:                 │    [red] Error build: {error}           │\n278:                 │    [if verbose] Full traceback          │\n279:                 │    Exit code: 1                         │\n280:                 └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n281: ```\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Data Structures\n286: \n287: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n288: \n289: Build command modifies and reads these fields:\n290: \n291: ```python\n292: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n293:     agent_name: str                      # Used for image name\n294:     description: Optional[str] = None\n295:     language: str = \"python\"\n296:     entrypoint: str                      # Dockerfile ENTRYPOINT\n297:     port: int = 8080                     # Dockerfile EXPOSE\n298:     build_mode: str = \"local\"            # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n299:     region: Optional[str] = None\n300:     version: Optional[str] = None        # Incremented on build\n301:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # Updated with build result\n302:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n303:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n304:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n305:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n306:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n307:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n308:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n309:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n310:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n311:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n312:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n313:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n314:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n315: \n316:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n317:     @classmethod\n318:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n319:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n320:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n321:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n322:         return v.lower()\n323: \n324:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n325:     @classmethod\n326:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n327:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n328:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n329:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n330:         return v.lower()\n331: \n332:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n333:     @classmethod\n334:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n335:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n336:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n337:         return v\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ### image Field Structure\n341: \n342: ```python\n343: image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = {\n344:     \"image_name\": str,       # e.g., \"my-agent\"\n345:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n346:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n347:     \"build_time\": float,     # Build duration in seconds\n348:     \"tag\": str,              # Image tag (e.g., \"v1.0.1\" or \"latest\")\n349: }\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ### BuildResult (Internal)\n353: \n354: ```python\n355: BuildResult = Dict[str, Any] = {\n356:     \"image_name\": str,\n357:     \"image_id\": str,\n358:     \"image_size\": str,\n359:     \"build_time\": float,\n360:     \"tag\": str,\n361:     \"success\": bool,\n362:     \"error\": Optional[str],\n363: }\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## API Contracts\n369: \n370: ### Command Interface\n371: \n372: | Command | Arguments | Description |\n373: |---------|-----------|-------------|\n374: | `build` | `--workspace` `-f` | Path to agent workspace directory (default: `.`) |\n375: | `build` | `--proxy` `-p` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n376: | `build` | `--cloud-provider` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n377: | `build` | `--output` | Output path for build artifacts |\n378: | `build` | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging |\n379: \n380: ### Typer Command Signature\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: @app.command()\n384: def build(\n385:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n386:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n387:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n388:         show_default=True\n389:     ),\n390:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n391:         None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\",\n392:         help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n393:     ),\n394:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n395:         None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n396:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n397:     ),\n398:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n399:         None, \"--output\",\n400:         help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n401:     ),\n402:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n403:         False, \"--verbose\",\n404:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"\n405:     ),\n406: ) -> None:\n407:     \"\"\"Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n408:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n409:     \n410:     with Progress(\n411:         SpinnerColumn(),\n412:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n413:         console=console,\n414:     ) as progress:\n415:         task = progress.add_task(\"Building agent image...\", total=None)\n416:         \n417:         try:\n418:             runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n419:             result = runtime.build(\n420:                 workspace_path,\n421:                 proxy=proxy,\n422:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n423:                 output=output,\n424:             )\n425:             progress.update(task, description=\"Build completed\")\n426:             \n427:             console.print(f\"[green]Build completed successfully[/green]\")\n428:             console.print(f\"Image: {result['image_name']}:{result['tag']}\")\n429:             console.print(f\"Image ID: {result['image_id']}\")\n430:             console.print(f\"Size: {result['image_size']}\")\n431:             console.print(f\"Build time: {result['build_time']}s\")\n432:             \n433:         except Exception as e:\n434:             progress.stop()\n435:             _handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ### BuildRuntime.build() Contract\n439: \n440: ```python\n441: def build(\n442:     self,\n443:     workspace_path: Path,\n444:     **options: Any,\n445: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n446:     \"\"\"\n447:     Build container image from workspace.\n448:     \n449:     Args:\n450:         workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n451:         options: Build options including:\n452:             - proxy: Optional[str] - Proxy URL for build args\n453:             - cloud_provider: Optional[str] - Cloud provider name\n454:             - output: Optional[str] - Output path\n455:     \n456:     Returns:\n457:         Dict containing:\n458:             - image_name: str\n459:             - image_id: str\n460:             - image_size: str\n461:             - build_time: float\n462:             - tag: str\n463:     \n464:     Raises:\n465:         RuntimeError: If Docker is not available\n466:         ValueError: If Dockerfile does not exist\n467:         RuntimeError: If build fails (version rolled back)\n468:     \"\"\"\n469: ```\n470: \n471: ### DockerService.build_image() Contract\n472: \n473: ```python\n474: def build_image(\n475:     self,\n476:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n477:     context_path: Path,\n478:     image_name: str,\n479:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n480:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n481: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n482:     \"\"\"\n483:     Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n484:     \n485:     Args:\n486:         dockerfile_path: Path to Dockerfile\n487:         context_path: Build context directory\n488:         image_name: Image name without tag\n489:         tag: Image tag\n490:         build_args: Optional build arguments (e.g., {\"PROXY\": url})\n491:     \n492:     Returns:\n493:         Dict containing:\n494:             - image_name: str (name:tag)\n495:             - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n496:             - image_size: str (human-readable)\n497:             - build_time: float (seconds)\n498:     \n499:     Raises:\n500:         docker.errors.BuildError: If build fails\n501:         docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API error\n502:     \"\"\"\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ---\n506: \n507: ## Error Handling\n508: \n509: ### Error Categories\n510: \n511: | Category | Condition | Action |\n512: |----------|-----------|--------|\n513: | Docker Unavailable | `docker.from_env()` fails | Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` |\n514: | Missing Dockerfile | No `Dockerfile` in workspace | Raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")` |\n515: | Build Failure | Docker build returns error | Rollback version, raise `RuntimeError` |\n516: | Invalid Metadata | Pydantic validation fails | Propagate `ValidationError` |\n517: | Version Rollback | Build fails after increment | Restore original version in metadata file |\n518: \n519: ### _handle_error() Pattern\n520: \n521: ```python\n522: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n523:     \"\"\"\n524:     Unified error handler for CLI commands.\n525:     \n526:     Prints error message in red, optionally shows traceback,\n527:     and exits with code 1.\n528:     \"\"\"\n529:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n530:     if verbose:\n531:         console.print_exception()\n532:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Version Rollback Logic\n536: \n537: ```python\n538: def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n539:     \"\"\"\n540:     Increment version with rollback capability.\n541:     \n542:     Returns new tag; caller must rollback on failure.\n543:     \"\"\"\n544:     original_version = metadata.version\n545:     try:\n546:         # Increment logic\n547:         if metadata.version:\n548:             if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(metadata.version):\n549:                 v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(metadata.version)\n550:                 new_version = str(v.bump_patch())\n551:             elif metadata.version.startswith(\"v\"):\n552:                 # v1.0 → v1.0.1\n553:                 base = metadata.version[1:]\n554:                 new_version = f\"v{base}.1\"\n555:             else:\n556:                 # Fallback: append -1\n557:                 new_version = f\"{metadata.version}-1\"\n558:         else:\n559:             new_version = \"latest\"\n560:         \n561:         metadata.version = new_version\n562:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n563:         return new_version\n564:         \n565:     except Exception:\n566:         metadata.version = original_version\n567:         raise\n568: ```\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## Testing Strategy\n573: \n574: ### Unit Tests\n575: \n576: | Test File | Coverage |\n577: |-----------|----------|\n578: | `tests/test_build_runtime.py` | BuildRuntime methods |\n579: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService methods |\n580: | `tests/test_version_increment.py` | Version bump edge cases |\n581: \n582: ### Test Cases\n583: \n584: #### BuildRuntime Tests\n585: \n586: ```python\n587: class TestBuildRuntime:\n588:     def test_build_local_success(self, mock_docker_service, mock_metadata):\n589:         \"\"\"Successful local build returns image info.\"\"\"\n590:         \n591:     def test_build_docker_unavailable(self, mock_docker_unavailable):\n592:         \"\"\"Raises RuntimeError when Docker not running.\"\"\"\n593:         \n594:     def test_build_missing_dockerfile(self, workspace_no_dockerfile):\n595:         \"\"\"Raises ValueError when Dockerfile missing.\"\"\"\n596:         \n597:     def test_version_increment_semver(self):\n598:         \"\"\"X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1) for valid semver.\"\"\"\n599:         \n600:     def test_version_increment_v_prefix(self):\n601:         \"\"\"v1.0 → v1.0.1 for v-prefixed versions.\"\"\"\n602:         \n603:     def test_version_increment_fallback(self):\n604:         \"\"\"custom → custom-1 for non-semver strings.\"\"\"\n605:         \n606:     def test_version_rollback_on_failure(self, mock_build_failure):\n607:         \"\"\"Original version restored when build fails.\"\"\"\n608:         \n609:     def test_build_cloud_placeholder(self):\n610:         \"\"\"Cloud build returns placeholder dict.\"\"\"\n611: ```\n612: \n613: #### DockerService Tests\n614: \n615: ```python\n616: class TestDockerService:\n617:     def test_check_docker_available_running(self, mock_docker_client):\n618:         \"\"\"Returns True when Docker daemon running.\"\"\"\n619:         \n620:     def test_check_docker_available_not_running(self):\n621:         \"\"\"Returns False when Docker daemon unavailable.\"\"\"\n622:         \n623:     def test_build_image_success(self, mock_docker_api):\n624:         \"\"\"build_image returns image info dict.\"\"\"\n625:         \n626:     def test_build_image_with_proxy(self, mock_docker_api):\n627:         \"\"\"Proxy passed as build_arg.\"\"\"\n628:         \n629:     def test_get_image_info(self, mock_image):\n630:         \"\"\"Extracts image_id and size.\"\"\"\n631:         \n632:     def test_push_image_with_auth(self, mock_registry):\n633:         \"\"\"Login and push with credentials.\"\"\"\n634:         \n635:     def test_remove_image_success(self, mock_image):\n636:         \"\"\"Returns True on removal.\"\"\"\n637:         \n638:     def test_remove_image_failure(self):\n639:         \"\"\"Returns False, logs warning.\"\"\"\n640: ```\n641: \n642: ### Integration Tests\n643: \n644: ```python\n645: class TestBuildIntegration:\n646:     def test_full_build_workflow(self, packaged_workspace):\n647:         \"\"\"End-to-end: validate → increment → build → update metadata.\"\"\"\n648:         \n649:     def test_build_after_pack(self, agent_workspace):\n650:         \"\"\"Pack creates Dockerfile, build succeeds.\"\"\"\n651:         \n652:     def test_rebuild_increments_version(self, built_workspace):\n653:         \"\"\"Second build bumps version again.\"\"\"\n654: ```\n655: \n656: ### Test Fixtures\n657: \n658: ```python\n659: @pytest.fixture\n660: def mock_docker_service():\n661:     \"\"\"Mock DockerService with fake client.\"\"\"\n662:     \n663: @pytest.fixture\n664: def packaged_workspace(tmp_path):\n665:     \"\"\"Temporary workspace with Dockerfile and metadata.\"\"\"\n666:     \n667: @pytest.fixture\n668: def mock_build_failure():\n669:     \"\"\"Mock Docker SDK to raise BuildError.\"\"\"\n670: ```\n671: \n672: ---\n673: \n674: ## File Structure\n675: \n676: ```\n677: cmd/cli/\n678: ├── pyproject.toml\n679: ├── agentcube/\n680: │   ├── __init__.py\n681: │   ├── cli/\n682: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n683: │   │   └── main.py              # build command addition\n684: │   ├── models/\n685: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n686: │   │   └── pack_models.py       # MetadataOptions (shared)\n687: │   ├── runtime/\n688: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n689: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n690: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py     # NEW: BuildRuntime\n691: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py   # Future\n692: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py    # Future\n693: │   │   └── status_runtime.py    # Future\n694: │   ├── services/\n695: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n696: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py  # Existing\n697: │   │   ├── docker_service.py    # NEW: DockerService\n698: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py      # Future\n699: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # Future\n700: │   └── operations/\n701: │       └── __init__.py\n702: ├── examples/\n703: │   ├── hello-agent/\n704: │   │   └── main.py\n705: │   └── math-agent/\n706: │       └── main.py\n707: └── tests/\n708:     ├── __init__.py\n709:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n710:     ├── test_build_runtime.py     # NEW\n711:     ├── test_docker_service.py    # NEW\n712:     └── test_version_increment.py # NEW\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## Dependencies\n718: \n719: ### Runtime Dependencies\n720: \n721: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n722: |---------|---------|---------|\n723: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; local build execution |\n724: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n725: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file I/O |\n726: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, console output |\n727: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic version parsing and bumping |\n728: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n729: \n730: ### Dev Dependencies\n731: \n732: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n733: |---------|---------|---------|\n734: | `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Test framework |\n735: | `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n736: | `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n737: | `pytest-mock` | `>=3.11.0` | Mocking fixtures |\n738: | `ruff` | `>=0.1.0` | Linting |\n739: | `mypy` | `>=1.5.0` | Type checking |\n740: \n741: ### Optional Dependencies\n742: \n743: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n744: |---------|---------|---------|\n745: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client (for publish command) |\n746: \n747: ---\n748: \n749: ## Implementation Notes\n750: \n751: ### Version Increment Strategy\n752: \n753: ```python\n754: def _increment_version(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n755:     \"\"\"\n756:     Semver bump strategy:\n757:     \n758:     1. Valid semver (X.Y.Z): bump_patch → X.Y.(Z+1)\n759:        Example: 1.2.3 → 1.2.4\n760:     \n761:     2. v-prefixed non-semver (vX.Y): append .1\n762:        Example: v1.0 → v1.0.1\n763:     \n764:     3. Non-semver string: append -1\n765:        Example: custom → custom-1\n766:     \n767:     4. None/empty: use \"latest\"\n768:     \"\"\"\n769:     import semver\n770:     \n771:     if not metadata.version:\n772:         return \"latest\"\n773:     \n774:     version_str = metadata.version\n775:     \n776:     if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(version_str.lstrip(\"v\")):\n777:         base = version_str.lstrip(\"v\")\n778:         v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(base)\n779:         new_v = v.bump_patch()\n780:         prefix = \"v\" if version_str.startswith(\"v\") else \"\"\n781:         return f\"{prefix}{new_v}\"\n782:     \n783:     if version_str.startswith(\"v\") and \".\" in version_str:\n784:         return f\"{version_str}.1\"\n785:     \n786:     return f\"{version_str}-1\"\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ### Docker Build Streaming\n790: \n791: ```python\n792: def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, \n793:                 image_name: str, tag: str, build_args: Optional[Dict]) -> Dict:\n794:     \"\"\"\n795:     Stream build logs for verbose output:\n796:     \"\"\"\n797:     import docker\n798:     import time\n799:     \n800:     client = docker.from_env()\n801:     full_tag = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n802:     start_time = time.time()\n803:     \n804:     build_kwargs = {\n805:         \"path\": str(context_path),\n806:         \"dockerfile\": str(dockerfile_path),\n807:         \"tag\": full_tag,\n808:         \"buildargs\": build_args,\n809:         \"decode\": True,\n810:     }\n811:     \n812:     for line in client.api.build(**build_kwargs):\n813:         if self.verbose and \"stream\" in line:\n814:             print(line[\"stream\"].strip())\n815:         if \"error\" in line:\n816:             raise docker.errors.BuildError(line[\"error\"], build_log)\n817:     \n818:     build_time = time.time() - start_time\n819:     \n820:     image = client.images.get(full_tag)\n821:     return {\n822:         \"image_name\": image_name,\n823:         \"image_id\": image.id,\n824:         \"image_size\": self._format_size(image.attrs[\"Size\"]),\n825:         \"build_time\": round(build_time, 2),\n826:         \"tag\": tag,\n827:     }\n828: ```\n829: \n830: ### Proxy Build Arg\n831: \n832: ```python\n833: def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, \n834:                  options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n835:     \"\"\"\n836:     Proxy handling:\n837:     \"\"\"\n838:     build_args = None\n839:     if options.get(\"proxy\"):\n840:         build_args = {\"PROXY\": options[\"proxy\"]}\n841:     \n842:     dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n843:     \n844:     return self.docker_service.build_image(\n845:         dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n846:         context_path=workspace_path,\n847:         image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n848:         tag=options.get(\"tag\", metadata.version or \"latest\"),\n849:         build_args=build_args,\n850:     )\n851: ```\n852: \n853: ### Metadata Update Pattern\n854: \n855: ```python\n856: def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata,\n857:                            build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None:\n858:     \"\"\"\n859:     Update metadata.image with build result:\n860:     \"\"\"\n861:     metadata.image = {\n862:         \"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"],\n863:         \"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"],\n864:         \"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"],\n865:         \"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"],\n866:         \"tag\": tag,\n867:     }\n868:     \n869:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n870: ```\n871: \n872: ### Rollback Pattern\n873: \n874: ```python\n875: def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n876:     \"\"\"\n877:     Full build with rollback:\n878:     \"\"\"\n879:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n880:     original_version = metadata.version\n881:     \n882:     self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n883:     \n884:     new_tag = self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n885:     \n886:     try:\n887:         if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n888:             result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n889:         else:\n890:             result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n891:         \n892:         self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result, new_tag)\n893:         return result\n894:         \n895:     except Exception as e:\n896:         # Rollback version\n897:         metadata.version = original_version\n898:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n899:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")\n900: ```\n901: \n902: ---\n903: \n904: ## References\n905: \n906: - cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n907: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (Requirement: `build` command)\n908: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n909: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n910: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n911: - semver Python: https://python-semver.readthedocs.io/\n912: - AR-020 — CLI pack command (prerequisite, generates Dockerfile)\n913: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build, uses image info)\n\n(End of file - total 913 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nBuild command for AgentCube CLI that constructs container images from packaged agent workspaces. Orchestrates the full build lifecycle: prerequisite validation, version increment, Docker SDK build execution, and metadata persistence.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md","time":{"start":1775875916944,"end":1775875916967}}}}
