{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876035419,"sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","part":{"id":"prt_d7a75d2ff001FpofGxC8mdEUdi","messageID":"msg_d7a7404e4001ccIECMUNgee80Z","sessionID":"ses_2858ca779ffeoBjkFwURapQkVB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7f2f5313ac0e41b2ac328e26c85305bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","content":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-024 — DockerService 封装 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n`DockerService` encapsulates Docker SDK operations for container image lifecycle management: availability checks, image building, metadata retrieval, registry push with authentication, and image removal. It provides a clean abstraction layer between CLI runtime classes and the Docker Python SDK.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User CLI                                 │\n│  kubectl-agentcube build -f ./agent                             │\n│  kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./agent                           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Runtime Layer                                │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ BuildRuntime                                              │   │\n│  │  - build() → calls DockerService.build_image()            │   │\n│  │  - _validate_prerequisites() → check_docker_available()   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ PublishRuntime                                             │   │\n│  │  - _prepare_local_image() → DockerService.push_image()    │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    DockerService                                 │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ DockerService(verbose=False)                              │   │\n│  │  - _client: Any (lazy-loaded DockerClient)                │   │\n│  │  - check_docker_available() → bool                        │   │\n│  │  - build_image(...) → Dict[str, Any]                      │   │\n│  │  - get_image_info(...) → Dict[str, Any]                   │   │\n│  │  - push_image(...) → Dict[str, Any]                       │   │\n│  │  - remove_image(...) → bool                               │   │\n│  │  - _format_size(bytes) → str                              │   │\n│  │  - _get_client() → DockerClient                           │   │\n│  │  - build_image_legacy(...) → Dict[str, Any]               │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Docker Python SDK                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ docker.from_env() → DockerClient                          │   │\n│  │  - client.ping() → bool                                   │   │\n│  │  - client.images.build(...) → (Image, logs)               │   │\n│  │  - client.images.get(name) → Image                        │   │\n│  │  - client.images.push(name) → logs                        │   │\n│  │  - client.images.remove(name) → None                      │   │\n│  │  - client.login(...) → None                               │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Docker Daemon (dockerd)                       │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Docker Engine API                                          │   │\n│  │  - /_ping                                                  │   │\n│  │  - /build                                                  │   │\n│  │  - /images/{name}/json                                     │   │\n│  │  - /images/{name}/push                                     │   │\n│  │  - /images/{name} (DELETE)                                 │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         agentcube/services/                         │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                     │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    DockerService                              │  │\n│  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  │\n│  │ Instance Fields:                                              │  │\n│  │   - verbose: bool                                             │  │\n│  │   - _client: Any (private, lazy-loaded)                       │  │\n│  │                                                               │  │\n│  │ Public Methods:                                               │  │\n│  │   + check_docker_available() → bool                          │  │\n│  │   + build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path,                │  │\n│  │                  image_name, tag, build_args, verbose)        │  │\n│  │     → Dict[str, Any]                                          │  │\n│  │   + get_image_info(image_name, tag) → Dict[str, Any]         │  │\n│  │   + push_image(image_name, registry_url,                     │  │\n│  │                 username, password) → Dict[str, Any]         │  │\n│  │   + remove_image(image_name) → bool                           │  │\n│  │                                                               │  │\n│  │ Private Methods:                                              │  │\n│  │   - _get_client() → Any                                      │  │\n│  │   - _format_size(size_bytes: int) → str                      │  │\n│  │                                                               │  │\n│  │ Legacy Method:                                                │  │\n│  │   + build_image_legacy(workspace_path, metadata,             │  │\n│  │                        tag, buildargs) → Dict[str, Any]       │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                     │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nBuildRuntime.build()\n         │\n         ▼\nDockerService.check_docker_available()\n         │\n         ├─ docker.from_env() → client\n         ├─ client.ping() → True/False\n         │\n         ▼\nDockerService.build_image(\n    dockerfile_path=Path(\"./Dockerfile\"),\n    context_path=Path(\"./workspace\"),\n    image_name=\"my-agent\",\n    tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n    build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy:8080\"},\n    verbose=True\n)\n         │\n         ├─ _get_client() → client (lazy load)\n         ├─ time.time() → start_time\n         ├─ client.images.build(\n         │      path=str(context_path),\n         │      dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n         │      tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n         │      buildargs=build_args\n         │  ) → (Image, build_logs)\n         ├─ [if verbose] stream build_logs\n         ├─ time.time() → build_time\n         ├─ image.attrs[\"Size\"] → size_bytes\n         ├─ _format_size(size_bytes) → \"125.3 MB\"\n         │\n         ▼\nReturn Dict:\n{\n    \"image_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"image_id\": \"sha256:abc123...\",\n    \"image_size\": \"125.3 MB\",\n    \"build_time\": 45.2,\n    \"tag\": \"v1.0.0\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### BuildImageResult\n\n```python\nBuildImageResult = TypedDict(\"BuildImageResult\", {\n    \"image_name\": str,       # Image name without tag\n    \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n    \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n    \"build_time\": float,     # Build duration in seconds\n    \"tag\": str,              # Image tag (e.g., \"v1.0.0\" or \"latest\")\n})\n```\n\n### GetImageInfoResult\n\n```python\nGetImageInfoResult = TypedDict(\"GetImageInfoResult\", {\n    \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n    \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size\n})\n```\n\n### PushImageResult\n\n```python\nPushImageResult = TypedDict(\"PushImageResult\", {\n    \"pushed_image\": str,     # Full image name with registry URL\n    \"push_time\": float,      # Push duration in seconds\n})\n```\n\n### Size Format Thresholds\n\n| Range | Format | Example |\n|-------|--------|---------|\n| `< 1024` | `\"{n} B\"` | `\"500 B\"` |\n| `< 1024*1024` | `\"{n/1024:.1f} KB\"` | `\"1.0 KB\"` |\n| `< 1024*1024*1024` | `\"{n/(1024*1024):.1f} MB\"` | `\"1.0 MB\"` |\n| `>= 1024*1024*1024` | `\"{n/(1024*1024*1024):.1f} GB\"` | `\"1.0 GB\"` |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### check_docker_available()\n\n```python\ndef check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check if Docker daemon is running and accessible.\n    \n    Implementation:\n        - Import docker SDK\n        - Create client from environment (docker.from_env())\n        - Call client.ping()\n        \n    Returns:\n        True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n    \n    Note:\n        Catches all exceptions and returns False (no exception propagation).\n        Used for prerequisite validation in build/publish commands.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### build_image()\n\n```python\ndef build_image(\n    self,\n    dockerfile_path: Path,\n    context_path: Path,\n    image_name: str,\n    tag: Optional[str] = \"latest\",\n    build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    verbose: bool = False,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n    \n    Args:\n        dockerfile_path: Path to Dockerfile\n        context_path: Build context directory\n        image_name: Image name without tag\n        tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n        build_args: Optional build arguments (e.g., {\"HTTP_PROXY\": url})\n        verbose: Stream build logs to stdout\n    \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n            - image_name: str (name without tag)\n            - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n            - image_size: str (human-readable)\n            - build_time: float (seconds)\n            - tag: str\n    \n    Raises:\n        docker.errors.BuildError: If build fails\n        docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API error\n        Exception: Any other error (propagated with context)\n    \n    Implementation:\n        - Uses client.images.build() with path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs\n        - Measures elapsed time with time.time()\n        - Streams logs if verbose=True\n        - Formats size with _format_size()\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### get_image_info()\n\n```python\ndef get_image_info(self, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\") -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieve image metadata from Docker.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Image name without tag\n        tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n    \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n            - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n            - image_size: str (human-readable)\n    \n    Raises:\n        docker.errors.ImageNotFound: If image not found\n        Exception: Any other error (propagated)\n    \n    Note:\n        Full name constructed as f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n        Uses client.images.get(full_name)\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### push_image()\n\n```python\ndef push_image(\n    self,\n    image_name: str,\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    username: Optional[str] = None,\n    password: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Push Docker image to registry.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Full image name (may include tag)\n        registry_url: Optional registry URL (prepended to image_name)\n        username: Registry username (for login)\n        password: Registry password (for login)\n    \n    Returns:\n        Dict containing:\n            - pushed_image: str (full image name with registry)\n            - push_time: float (seconds)\n    \n    Implementation:\n        1. If username/password/registry_url provided:\n           - client.login(username, password, registry=registry_url)\n        2. Construct full image name:\n           - If registry_url: f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n           - Else: image_name\n        3. client.images.push(full_image_name)\n        4. Measure elapsed time\n    \n    Note:\n        Login is optional; assumes pre-authenticated Docker if credentials omitted.\n        Push logs are not streamed (may be extended in future).\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### remove_image()\n\n```python\ndef remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Remove Docker image from local daemon.\n    \n    Args:\n        image_name: Full image name (may include tag)\n    \n    Returns:\n        True if removal succeeded, False on any error.\n    \n    Note:\n        Does not propagate exceptions; logs warning if verbose.\n        Used for cleanup in error recovery scenarios.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### _get_client() (Private)\n\n```python\ndef _get_client(self) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"\n    Lazy-load Docker client instance.\n    \n    Returns:\n        DockerClient from docker.from_env()\n    \n    Note:\n        Client cached in self._client for reuse.\n        Import docker inside method (lazy import).\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### _format_size() (Private)\n\n```python\ndef _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Convert byte count to human-readable string.\n    \n    Args:\n        size_bytes: Size in bytes\n    \n    Returns:\n        Human-readable size string (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n    \n    Thresholds:\n        - Bytes: < 1024\n        - KB: < 1024*1024\n        - MB: < 1024*1024*1024\n        - GB: >= 1024*1024*1024\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### build_image_legacy() (Legacy)\n\n```python\ndef build_image_legacy(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    tag: Optional[str] = None,\n    buildargs: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Legacy build method for backward compatibility.\n    \n    Args:\n        workspace_path: Path to workspace (contains Dockerfile)\n        metadata: AgentMetadata with agent_name, version\n        tag: Override tag (uses metadata.version or \"latest\")\n        buildargs: Build arguments\n    \n    Returns:\n        Same as build_image()\n    \n    Note:\n        Delegates to build_image() with derived parameters:\n        - dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        - context_path = workspace_path\n        - image_name = metadata.agent_name\n        - tag = tag or metadata.version or \"latest\"\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Category | Condition | Action | Propagated? |\n|----------|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| Docker Unavailable | `docker.from_env()` fails or `ping()` fails | Return `False` | No (swallowed) |\n| Build Failure | `client.images.build()` raises | Print verbose message, raise | Yes |\n| Image Not Found | `client.images.get()` fails | Print verbose message, raise | Yes |\n| Push Failure | `client.images.push()` raises | Raise exception | Yes |\n| Login Failure | `client.login()` raises | Propagate | Yes |\n| Remove Failure | `client.images.remove()` raises | Log warning, return `False` | No |\n| Generic SDK Error | Any `docker.errors.*` | Propagate with context | Yes |\n\n### Exception Types\n\n| Exception | Source | Handling |\n|-----------|--------|----------|\n| `docker.errors.BuildError` | `build_image()` | Propagate; caller handles |\n| `docker.errors.APIError` | Any SDK call | Propagate |\n| `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | `get_image_info()` | Propagate |\n| `Exception` (generic) | Any method | Propagate or swallow based on method |\n\n### Verbose Logging\n\n```python\n# check_docker_available: no verbose output\n# build_image: verbose streams build logs\nif verbose:\n    for log in build_logs:\n        if \"stream\" in log:\n            print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n\n# get_image_info: verbose prints error\nif self.verbose:\n    print(f\"Error getting image info: {e}\")\nraise\n\n# build_image failure: verbose prints timing\nif verbose:\n    print(f\"Build failed after {build_time:.1f}s: {e}\")\nraise\n\n# remove_image: verbose would log warning (currently silent)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `tests/test_docker_service.py` | All DockerService methods |\n\n### Test Cases\n\n#### Initialization Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_init_default_verbose` | `DockerService()` | `verbose == False` |\n| `test_init_verbose_true` | `DockerService(verbose=True)` | `verbose == True` |\n\n#### check_docker_available Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_docker_available` | Mock `docker.from_env()` → ping returns True | Returns `True` |\n| `test_docker_unavailable` | Mock `docker.from_env()` raises Exception | Returns `False` |\n\n#### _format_size Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| `test_format_size_bytes` | `500` | `\"500 B\"` |\n| `test_format_size_kb` | `1024` | `\"1.0 KB\"` |\n| `test_format_size_mb` | `1048576` | `\"1.0 MB\"` |\n| `test_format_size_gb` | `1073741824` | `\"1.0 GB\"` |\n| `test_format_size_large_mb` | `125300000` | `\"~119.3 MB\"` |\n\n#### get_image_info Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_get_image_info_success` | Mock client.images.get() returns image | Dict with `image_id`, `image_size` |\n| `test_get_image_info_not_found` | Mock raises \"Image not found\" | Exception raised |\n\n#### build_image Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_build_image_basic` | Mock build returns image | Dict with all fields, correct tag |\n| `test_build_image_with_proxy` | Pass build_args with HTTP_PROXY | Build called with buildargs |\n| `test_build_image_default_tag` | No tag specified | Tag defaults to \"latest\" |\n| `test_build_image_failure` | Mock build raises Exception | Exception raised, verbose printed |\n\n#### push_image Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_push_image_basic` | No registry/credentials | `pushed_image` == input name |\n| `test_push_image_with_registry` | registry_url provided | `pushed_image` includes registry |\n| `test_push_image_with_auth` | username/password provided | `client.login()` called |\n\n#### remove_image Tests\n\n| Test Case | Scenario | Expected |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| `test_remove_image_success` | Mock remove succeeds | Returns `True` |\n| `test_remove_image_failure` | Mock remove raises Exception | Returns `False` |\n\n### Mock Strategy\n\n```python\n# Docker client mock pattern\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_client():\n    with patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n        mock_client = MagicMock()\n        mock_client.ping.return_value = True\n        mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n        mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n        mock_client.images.push.return_value = []\n        mock_client.images.remove.return_value = None\n        mock_client.login.return_value = None\n        mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n        yield mock_client\n\n# Image mock\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_image():\n    image = MagicMock()\n    image.id = \"sha256:abc123def456\"\n    image.attrs = {\"Size\": 125300000}\n    return image\n\n# _get_client override pattern\nwith patch.object(service, '_get_client') as mock_get:\n    mock_get.return_value = mock_client\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   └── services/\n│       ├── __init__.py              # Services package marker\n│       ├── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│       ├── docker_service.py        # DockerService (AR-024)\n│       ├── k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider (future)\n│       └── agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider (future)\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_docker_service.py       # DockerService unit tests\n    ├── test_build_runtime.py        # BuildRuntime (uses DockerService)\n    └── test_publish_runtime.py      # PublishRuntime (uses DockerService)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; client.from_env(), images API |\n| `typing` | (stdlib) | Optional, Dict, Any type hints |\n| `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path for file path handling |\n| `time` | (stdlib) | time.time() for duration measurement |\n\n### pyproject.toml Entry\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    ...\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Lazy Client Loading\n\n```python\ndef _get_client(self) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"\n    Docker client is lazily loaded on first use.\n    \n    Benefits:\n    - Avoids import error at module load if docker SDK unavailable\n    - Single client instance reused across multiple operations\n    - Allows check_docker_available() to test SDK availability separately\n    \"\"\"\n    import docker\n    if self._client is None:\n        self._client = docker.from_env()\n    return self._client\n```\n\n### Size Formatting Thresholds\n\n| Threshold | Calculation | Example |\n|-----------|-------------|---------|\n| Bytes | `size_bytes < 1024` | `500 → \"500 B\"` |\n| KB | `size_bytes < 1024*1024` | `2048 → \"2.0 KB\"` |\n| MB | `size_bytes < 1024*1024*1024` | `5242880 → \"5.0 MB\"` |\n| GB | `size_bytes >= 1024*1024*1024` | `2147483648 → \"2.0 GB\"` |\n\n### Build Args Convention\n\n```python\n# Proxy build arguments passed to Dockerfile\nbuild_args = {\n    \"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n    \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n}\n\n# Dockerfile must ARG these:\n# ARG HTTP_PROXY\n# ARG HTTPS_PROXY\n```\n\n### Registry URL Construction\n\n```python\n# Prepend registry URL to image name\nif registry_url:\n    full_image_name = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\nelse:\n    full_image_name = image_name\n\n# Example:\n# image_name = \"my-agent:latest\"\n# registry_url = \"registry.example.com\"\n# → full_image_name = \"registry.example.com/my-agent:latest\"\n```\n\n### Verbose Build Streaming\n\n```python\n# Build logs streamed line-by-line\nfor log in build_logs:\n    if \"stream\" in log:\n        print(log[\"stream\"].strip())\n\n# Example log format:\n# {\"stream\": \"Step 1/5 : FROM python:3.10-slim\\n\"}\n# {\"stream\": \" ---> abc123def456\\n\"}\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (Docker integration requirements)\n- Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n- Docker Engine API: https://docs.docker.com/engine/api/\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService.push_image)\n- docker.errors module: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/errors.html"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775876035386,"end":1775876035416}}}}
